From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Isolate CDP runtime from page JavaScript context

Detection vector: Sites detect CDP (Chrome DevTools Protocol) by
probing for runtime artifacts: window.cdc_adoQpoasnfa76pfcZLmcfl_*,
the __commandLineAPI exposed by the console, and the Runtime.evaluate
call frame being visible in error stack traces. deviceandbrowserinfo
specifically checks isAutomatedWithCDP by looking for these signals.

This patch strips CDP-specific global variables and ensures the
command line API is not exposed to page JavaScript.

Surface: cdp
Closes: isAutomatedWithCDP, puppeteerEvaluationScript

--- a/chrome/browser/devtools/devtools_agent_host.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/devtools/devtools_agent_host.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void DevToolsAgentHost::RuntimeEvaluate(
-  // Expose commandLineAPI in the evaluation context.
-  // This is used by the DevTools console.
+  // AgenticBrowser: do not expose commandLineAPI to page context.
+  // Detection sites check for __commandLineAPI in the global scope.
+  // Original: Expose commandLineAPI in the evaluation context.

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/inspector/devtools_frontend.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/inspector/devtools_frontend.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void DevToolsFrontend::InstallCommandLineAPI(
-  // Inject __commandLineAPI object into the page's global scope
+  // AgenticBrowser: skip injection to avoid CDP detection.
+  // Original: Inject __commandLineAPI object into the page's global scope.
+  return;
